g.text: This IPSO object should be used for a speaker that plays a
pre-recorded audio clip or an audio output that is sent elsewhere.
For example, an elevator which announces the floor of the building. A
resource is provided to store the clip, a dimmer resource controls
the relative sound level of the playback, and a duration resource
limits the maximum playback time. After the duration time is reached,
any remaining samples in the clip are ignored, and the clip player
will be ready to play another clip.
